file=Engineering/mia/logical/book-requirements.md · h=name: book-requirements\ntype: logical (placeholder — awaiting operator-supplied source books per rule 0.6)\nassigned_agent: mia (Engineering / Frontend Web)\ndate_added: 2026-07-09\n · p:=The logical layer grounds mia's judgments in real, citable sources. mia's accessibility standard (WCAG) and Core Web Vitals are already externally sourced; the books below ground the parts convention supplies.\n · ca:sources (operator to supply; suggestions, not purchases mia made)=1. **WCAG guidelines** (already the cited a11y standard) — the authoritative accessibility reference; keep current (dated, like a platform playbook).\n2. **A frontend-architecture / component-design text** — grounds ui-accessibility-standards' component-system reasoning and state management beyond convention.\n3. **Web performance / Core Web Vitals reference** (Google's published thresholds + a perf-engineering text) — grounds frontend-performance's targets and diagnosis; shared signal with rank.\n · cf:as reasoning-based (rule 0.6)=- Component-system structure decisions when no library exists yet.\n- Core Web Vitals TARGETS when config is unset (Google publishes thresholds — cite them; the per-business target is operator-set).\n- Bundle-budget values before ops baselines exist.\n · ep:(when books arrive)=Standards/thresholds extracted with citations into this folder; ui-accessibility-standards and frontend-performance updated to cite them; reasoning-based flags removed where a citation replaces them. WCAG and Core Web Vitals thresholds stay dated (they update). Coordinate the perf reference with rank (shared Core Web Vitals signal).\n